Of note pt was difficult to obtain a history from and there is little consistency between his story on admission and what was recorded by his PCP in his S chart . Pt states he has had increasing LE swelling for 2 weeks despite taking all of his medications . Pt states that he has not increased his Na intake recently . Pt repeatedly denied SOB , increased abd girth , and PND . Pt did note that he sleeps on 2 pillows at night but his breathing his fine when he is lying flat . Next day spoke with patient 's wife who confirmed story documented by PCP including increasing shorntness of breath and orthopnea . ED : lasix 120 IV x 1 ROS : no fevers , chills , or night sweats . No ST , hearing problems , or visual problems . No SOB , but does note non-productive cough x 1 day . No CP , palpitations , orthopnea , or PND . No abd pain , N / V , diarrhea , BRBPR . Pt does endorse nocturia stating that he gets up 6 - 7 times / night to urinate . No dysuria or hematuria . No joint pains or rashes . - - - - - PMH : OSA DM - on insulin HTN Anemia H / o DVT - on coumadin ? CHF - per old SMH notes H / o pituitary adenoma and hyperprolactinemia BPH - - - - - ALL : AceI - - > angioedema ( required trach ) , PCN - - > rash - - - - - MEDS : ( per PH note , unclear what he 's actually taking , if any ) Atenolol 100mg po daily Protonix 40mg po daily Catapres 0.2 mg tp daily ( although no patch on body ) Lasix 120mg po bid Norvasc 10mg po daily Lantus ( dose unknown ) Singulair 10mg po daily Beconase aq 1 spray / nostril tid - - - - - SH : Pt lives with wife . No tob , EtOH , or drug use . - - - - - FH : non-contributory - - - - - PE on Admit : VS : 96.4 63 138 / 74 24 96 % on 2.5 LNC Gen : A & O , NAD , comfortable breathing while lying flat , loud breathing HEENT : PERRL , EOMI , OP clear , MM dry Neck : lot of redundant neck tissue , could not appreciate JVP , supple CV : nl s1 s2 , no m / r / g Lungs : CTA - bilat , no crackles , no dullness Abd : obese , NT / ND , quiet BS , lg midline surgical scar with other surrounding scars Extrem : 1 - 2 + pitting edema to knees , WWP , no cyanosis - - - - - PROC / TESTS : CXR : negative ( prelim ) Echo ( 4 / 3 ) - marked LVH , otherwise nl , EF 55 - 70 % Echo ( 3 / 22 ) - mod LVH , EF 60 - 65 % , no WMAs , suggestive of diastolic dysfunction , trace TR - - - - - CONSULTS : Pulmonary Medicine ( Dr. Kohlmeyer ) - - - - - IMP : 71 yo male with h / o DM , HTN , and poss h / o CHF who presents with 2 weeks of LE edema . - - - - - PLAN : CARDS : I : No known h / o CAD - little concern for ACS with no sxs except LE edema - unclear why not on ASA , no h / o GI bleed or ulcer . Will start ASA for primary / secondary prevention . Checked lipid profile , trigs very elevated at 482 and HDL 24 . LDL could not be peformed b / c trigs were so high . Started gemfibrozil , pt can have repeat lipid profile as outpt and statin at discretion of PCP . Pt was continued on BB but dose was decreased to 50mg po daily as pt having asymptomatic bradycardia to 40's while sleeping . P : Pt 's OS notes list CHF as dx , pt denies any h / o LE edema or CHF before 2 weeks ago but is on lasix bid at home . Last echo in 4 / 3 showed LVH w / preserved EF . Pt with likely diastolic dysfunction . Pt on exam has only LE edema , but received 120 IV lasix in ED . Pt 's presentation c / w CHF exacerbation but BNP of 13 is unusual . Continued to diurese pt with IV lasix and once he was approaching euvolemia switched him back over to home dose . Pt 's LE edema likely multifactorial due to CHF and some component of chronic venous stasis . LENIs were checked and were negative for DVTS . Discontinued pt 's CCB as may be contributing to LE edema . Echo was repeated this admit which showed EF 60 - 65 % and signs of diastolic dysfunction . HTN : BP was controlled this admit . Pt was continued on BB , norvasc , & catapres R : no issues this admit ENDO : Pt has h / o DM and pt states he is taking insulin at home ( unclear dose ) . Pt was started on Lantus with SS novolog and his sugars were somewhat elevated . Advised pt to restart home insulin regimen after d / c . Sent HgA1C but was still pending at the time of discharge . RENAL : pt appears to have CKD per SHC recs - baseline 1.4 - 1.6 , renally dose meds NEURO : Pt 's wife noted that pt has intermittently been confused at home . She describes episodes when he wakes up at night and does n't know where he is . This is likely due to hypoxia as pt has severe sleep apnea and rarely wears cpap at home . Pt was alert and oriented during this admit . Sent labs to evaluate for secondary cause of dementia and they were negative . Suggested that pt f / u with PCP if these episodes persist . PULM : Pt with h / o sleep apnea . Per 2003 sleep study pt 's sleep apnea was central and not obstructive although this is difficult to believe based on pt 's body habitus and redundant neck tissue . Pt evaluated by pulmonary after RA ABG showed PaO2 50's . Pt pulse ox was monitored and when he fell asleep without his cpap he desatted to low 60's and high 50's . Pt satted in mid 90's on RA while awake and upright . Pulmonary thought pt likely with obesity hypoventilation syndrome and sleep apnea ( central + / - obstructive ) . Pt tried on empiric bipap ( 4 / 9 ) the night prior to d / c and felt that he slept much better . Of note pt used the nasal mask in house but has the full mask at home . Tried to set up pt for home bipap but is not eligible unless has another sleep study . Communicated this with pt 's PCP who will set up repeat sleep study in near future . Pt also started on empiric qhs acetazolamide per pulmonary recs based on recent data showing that it improves symptoms in pt 's with central sleep apnea and heart failure . PPx : lovenox CODE : FULL FULL ADDITIONAL COMMENTS : DISCHARGE CONDITION : Stable TO DO / PLAN : No dictated summary ENTERED BY : LAGUE , RICHARD F. , M.D. ( PZ89 ) 6 / 13 / 06 @ 04 * * * * * * END OF DISCHARGE ORDERS * * * * * *
